itemListElement.name: Bainbridge Island Nature Reserve Walk with Lunch

name: Bainbridge Island Nature Reserve Walk with Lunch
description: Explore a beautiful garden after a peaceful ride across Puget Sound on the ferry. Bainbridge Island has a beautiful garden and forest park with old growth trees and various gardens. With an abundance of Pacific Northwest foliage, a stream, a pond, and several easy trails, it's beautiful. Choose among several quality restaurant choices.

itemListElement.name: Native Culture - Suquamish and Chief Seattle

name: Native Culture - Suquamish and Chief Seattle
description: Start the day with a ferry ride to Bainbridge Island, visit Chief Seattle's grave, and visit the Suquamish Indians Museum and views of Puget Sound. A very informative cultural experience.

review.name: Fantastic Tour.
review.reviewBody:
Cheryl was our tour guide and safe driver on this very interesting trip that focused on the culture and history of the local Suquamish Indians and the great Chief Seattle.
She was one of the most personable and friendly person I got to meet in the tour business, full of knowledge and easy to talk to. We started the day with an on time hotel pickup, followed by a ferry trip to Bainbridge Island and a short drive to the Suquamish Reservation. After visiting Chief Seattle’s gravesite we went to the tribal museum,where a tribal docent explained us the exhibits and answered our questions about the history and present situation of the tribe. A lunch in a restaurant overlooking the marina concluded our time on Bainbridge Island. After the trip back with the ferry Cheryl brought us back to our hotel. Thank you Cheryl for a great day.

itemListElement.name: NW Trek - See Wild Animals in Natural Habitat

itemListElement.name: Private Seattle Tour With Delectable NW Lunch

name: Private Seattle Tour With Delectable NW Lunch
description:
Seattle, all the sights and sounds, plus a delicious lunch!  

Discover Seattle's popular downtown attractions and area neighborhoods on this private, 5 hour city tour. Dine in one of Seattle's great restaurants (included) and learn the local and regional history in this vibrant and growing city, including the geology and current Northwest trends.

itemListElement.name: Olympic National Park, Snoqualmie Falls 2-Day Tour from Seattle

name: Olympic National Park, Snoqualmie Falls 2-Day Tour from Seattle
description:
Be inspired by the glacier-capped peaks, valleys of forests, hot springs, and rugged Pacific coastline.Get amazed by the magnificent Hurricane Ridge and Lake Crescent! Learn the history of Leavenworth, a German Town, with a glance at its unique Bavarian-inspired treasures.Try an authentic local German pork trotter meal with sausage and dark beer!

name: 1-Hour Family Treasure Cruise in Seattle
description: Our Family Treasure Cruise program is a 1-hour, fully interactive and choreographed experience focused on children but enjoyed by all ages. On-board activities include choosing a pirate name, learning to be a pirate, a treasure hunt, Epic Cannon Battle, treasure recovery (each child gets one item from the treasure chest), birthday song and pirate certificates.

review.name: Great experience, exceeded my expectations!
review.reviewBody:
I was little on the fence about spending the amount of money for a 1h thing, but this crew really went the extra mile with the experience! My 3.5 yo was maybe a bit young to understand the storyline and too shy to get fully into the action but she has been talking about how the pirate ship “was really fun” every day since we went.
Quality experience, great crew, entertaining for the adults, safe and fun. Definitely recommended for 5yo +

Only downside was that own snacks were not allowed and the selection in the ship was not the greatest or healthiest. I know it was just 1h but when 3yo wants a snack and are getting hangry this can be an issue…

review.name: Pirate Ship Sailing Success
review.reviewBody: I went on an Emerald City Pirate sailing last year with my 5 year old son. We had so much fun and he raved about it for months. This experience led me to book two pirate ship sailings for client events. One was geared more towards families, while the second was geared to adults. Everyone had a blast!  The organizers made everything so easy and they went beyond to ensure that my guests felt comfortable and included.  Highly recommend!!

itemListElement.name: Shuttle to Snoqualmie Pass Ski and Snowboard

name: Shuttle to Snoqualmie Pass Ski and Snowboard
description:
Join us on the seamless journey from Seattle to Snoqualmie Pass Ski Resort with our 4WD shuttle. Enjoy the convenience of pickup at your address and direct resort drop-offs. Our scenic route through snow-covered mountains and majestic waterways enhances your experience, starting your adventure the moment you board. 

Snacks included, 5-phone charging station onboard, and large navigation system to track the journey.

Prioritizing safety and comfort, our experienced drivers ensure a smooth ride for solo travelers and groups alike, making it the perfect choice for your ski trip. 

If you're booking as a group please send me Spotify playlists and inquire about karaoke options and I can bring the equipment along!

itemListElement.name: Seattle "Make a Mosaic" Crafts Event by Yaymaker

name: Seattle "Make a Mosaic" Crafts Event by Yaymaker
description:
Create coasters and trivets with flair at local bars and restaurants with Make a Mosaic events hosted by Yaymaker. Customers arrange brightly colored glass pieces on ceramic tile to create drink-and-food-saving statement pieces. Coasters and trivets keep your furniture safe, but that doesn’t mean they can’t look good while doing it! Create your own unique designs and make them for yourself, give as gifts, or even better, bring your friends and you’ll each have your own set. 

Make a Mosaic events are partnered with local restaurants and bars. After purchase, visit the website and choose your desired event. At the checkout page, simply enter your voucher code listed on your TripAdvisor confirmation email. Any remaining amount due is the experience fee for your event.

name: Pike Place Market Walking Ghost Tour
description: Learn about Pike Place Markets spooky side on this ghost tour. Follow a guide on a walk the market, including sites such as the underground market, an Irish Pub in an ancient mortuary, and dark hallways, all while listening to market lore. This ghost tour is a fun introduction to the market and spirits history. Speaking of spirits, your guide will be buying you some along the way.

review.name: Ghost tour
review.reviewBody: What a great tour! So fun and a great tour guide!! Couldn’t have imagined a better experience!! What a great way to spend a dreary afternoon!

review.name: Drinking Spirits with Spirits
review.reviewBody: We had a great time getting cocktails and talking about Pike Place ghost stories. Carolyn knows a lot about the market and its history, it was especially great to hear the native history.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Must-See Attractions Private Walking Tour with a Guide

name: Seattle Must-See Attractions Private Walking Tour with a Guide
description: Immerse yourself in the heart of Seattle with a walking tour led by a seasoned local guide. Begin your journey amidst the bustling energy of Pike Place Market, where vibrant stalls, fresh produce, and local artisans offer a glimpse into the city's dynamic culture. Traverse historic neighborhoods like Pioneer Square, tracing the city's evolution through its architecture and fascinating stories. Marvel at iconic landmarks such as the Space Needle, an architectural marvel that epitomizes Seattle's innovative spirit and skyline. As you wander through the city, indulge in the flavors of the region, sampling local delicacies like freshly caught seafood, artisanal cheeses, and world-renowned coffee that showcase Seattle's diverse culinary scene. Throughout the tour, your guide will weave together the past and present, offering a comprehensive understanding of Seattle's rich heritage and vibrant contemporary life.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Small Group Walking Tour with Space Needle Admission

name: Seattle Small Group Walking Tour with Space Needle Admission
description:
Welcome aboard the Best of Seattle Walking Tour. Our journey begins with the iconic Space Needle, where you’ll enjoy panoramic city views and marvel at this symbol of Seattle's innovative spirit. This architectural marvel offers a breathtaking vantage point of the city and surrounding landscapes.

Next, we embark on a scenic harbor cruise, providing unique perspectives of the waterfront and skyline. The refreshing sea air and rhythmic waves create a serene atmosphere, perfect for capturing memorable photos and experiencing Seattle from a different angle.

Our adventure then takes an intriguing turn underground with the Beneath the Streets experience. Explore hidden passages beneath Seattle, uncovering fascinating stories from the city's past and the Klondike Gold Rush era. As we traverse the city, we’ll pass landmarks like the historic Smith Tower, the eclectic Seattle Art Museum, and the bustling Pike Place Market. Join us for an unforgettable journey.

itemListElement.name: City Sightseeing Seattle HOHO Bus with Sky View Observatory Entry

name: City Sightseeing Seattle HOHO Bus with Sky View Observatory Entry
description:
Explore everything that Seattle has to offer onboard a City Sightseeing hop-on hop-off bus tour valid for either 24 or 48 hours. Create your own itinerary, hopping off at the sights 
that interest you the most. With an informative audio guide available in English, you'll learn lots of interesting facts and information about this city. Discover key landmarks such as Space Needle, Seattle Central Library, Pike Place Market and much more! Entry to Seattle Sky View Observatory is also included so you'll be able to look down on the city from a height of 275 meters! Use the observation deck - the highest viewing platform west of the Mississippi - to decide which parts of the city you'd like to visit.

itemListElement.name: Scenic Seattle Night Walking Tour with Space Needle Admission

name: Scenic Seattle Night Walking Tour with Space Needle Admission
description:
Dive into Seattle’s vibrant nightlife with our captivating tour, designed to unveil the city’s best-kept secrets. Begin your adventure at the iconic Space Needle, where you’ll be awestruck by its futuristic design and sweeping 360-degree views from the observation deck. 

Following our time at the Space Needle we head to the waterfront to Enjoy the Great Wheel. The iconic “Great Wheel”, known as the tallest wheel in the western United States, a captivating attraction that offers breathtaking views of Seattle's skyline and the sparkling waters of Elliott Bay. Step into one of the spacious cabins and ascend high above the city, taking in the panoramic vistas that will leave you awe-inspired. Feel the gentle breeze as you rotate gracefully, capturing Instagram-worthy photos and creating lasting memories.

Join TripShepherd for this great night experience, an immersive adventure that showcases the highlights of this vibrant city.

itemListElement.name: Private Street Food Tour With A Local Guide in Seattle

name: Private Street Food Tour With A Local Guide in Seattle
description: Experience Seattle's culinary and cultural treasures with a tour that begins at the heart of the city's gastronomic scene, Pike Place Market. Here, you’ll savor the flavors of the Pacific Northwest, from the velvety richness of clam chowder to decadent cheesecake laced with Colombian chocolate. As you wander through the market, artisans share their crafts, revealing hidden gems like local sweets and fresh seafood, while the bustling energy of North Pacific fishing traditions surrounds you. The adventure continues with breathtaking views from the Space Needle, where the cityscape unfolds beneath you. Explore the Chihuly Garden and Glass, a kaleidoscope of color and light, before concluding at the Seattle Waterfront, where the city's maritime legacy meets modern-day charm. This journey offers not just a feast for the senses but an immersive dive into Seattle's vibrant culture.

itemListElement.name: City Sightseeing Seattle Hop-On Hop-Off Bus Tour and Locks Cruise

name: City Sightseeing Seattle Hop-On Hop-Off Bus Tour and Locks Cruise
description: Hop-on a City Sightseeing bus tour to explore Seattle at your own pace. With 24 and 48-hour tickets available, you can choose the option that suits you best. With an informative audio guide in English onboard the bus, you'll learn plenty of interesting facts about Seattle. Sit back, relax and enjoy sights such as Space Needle, Seattle Central Library, Seattle Sky View Observatory and Pike Place Market to name a few! Included in your ticket is a 2-hour one-way Locks Cruise and an audio-guided walking tour can that be downloaded to your smartphone. You'll learn all about Seattle's early days and images of the objects being talked about will be displayed on your screen. Book your City Sightseeing ticket today!

review.name: Great job showing me the key sites in Seattle!
